#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn8.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn8.2:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn8.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Vaṅgīsavagga "
msgstr "1. With Vaṅgīsa "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 2. Aratīsutta → aratisuttaṃ (bj, s1-3) | arai (pts1)
msgctxt "sn8.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Aratīsutta "
msgstr "2. Dissatisfaction "

# NOTE: The pe seems odd here.
#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.401, sc1
msgctxt "sn8.2:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ … pe … āyasmā vaṅgīso āḷaviyaṃ viharati aggāḷave cetiye āyasmatā nigrodhakappena upajjhāyena saddhiṃ. "
msgstr "At one time Venerable Vaṅgīsa was staying near Āḷavī, at the Aggāḷava Tree-shrine, together with his mentor, Venerable Nigrodhakappa. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn8.2:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā nigrodhakappo pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto vihāraṃ pavisati, sāyaṃ vā nikkhamati aparajju vā kāle. "
msgstr "Now at that time after Venerable Nigrodhakappa had finished his meal, on his return from alms-round, he would enter his dwelling and not emerge for the rest of that day, or the next. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn8.2:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato vaṅgīsassa anabhirati uppannā hoti, rāgo cittaṃ anuddhaṃseti. "
msgstr "And at that time Venerable Vaṅgīsa became dissatisfied, as lust infected his mind. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn8.2:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato vaṅgīsassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then he thought, "

msgctxt "sn8.2:1.5"
msgid "“alābhā vata me, na vata me lābhā; dulladdhaṃ vata me, na vata me suladdhaṃ; "
msgstr "“It’s my loss, my misfortune, "

msgctxt "sn8.2:1.6"
msgid "yassa me anabhirati uppannā, rāgo cittaṃ anuddhaṃseti; taṃ kutettha labbhā, yaṃ me paro anabhiratiṃ vinodetvā abhiratiṃ uppādeyya. "
msgstr "that I’ve become dissatisfied, with lust infecting my mind. How is it possible for someone else to dispel my discontent and give rise to satisfaction? "

msgctxt "sn8.2:1.7"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ attanāva attano anabhiratiṃ vinodetvā abhiratiṃ uppādeyyan”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I do it myself?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn8.2:1.8"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā vaṅgīso attanāva attano anabhiratiṃ vinodetvā abhiratiṃ uppādetvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imā gāthāyo abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then, on the occasion of dispelling his own discontent and giving rise to satisfaction, he recited these verses: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn8.2:2.1"
msgid "“Aratiñca ratiñca pahāya, "
msgstr "“Giving up discontent and desire, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.2:2.2"
msgid "Sabbaso gehasitañca vitakkaṃ; "
msgstr "along with all thoughts of the lay life, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.2:2.3"
msgid "Vanathaṃ na kareyya kuhiñci, "
msgstr "they wouldn’t get entangled in anything; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.2:2.4"
msgid "Nibbanatho arato sa hi bhikkhu. "
msgstr "unentangled, undesiring: that’s a real mendicant. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn8.2:3.1"
msgid "Yamidha pathaviñca vehāsaṃ, "
msgstr "Whether on this earth or in the sky, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.2:3.2"
msgid "Rūpagatañca jagatogadhaṃ; "
msgstr "whatever in the world is included in form "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.2:3.3"
msgid "Kiñci parijīyati sabbamaniccaṃ, "
msgstr "wears out, it is all impermanent; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.2:3.4"
msgid "Evaṃ samecca caranti mutattā. "
msgstr "the thoughtful live having comprehended this truth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.402, sc4
#. VAR: gadhitāse → gadhitā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn8.2:4.1"
msgid "Upadhīsu janā gadhitāse, "
msgstr "People are bound to their attachments, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.2:4.2"
msgid "Diṭṭhasute paṭighe ca mute ca; "
msgstr "to what is seen, heard, felt, and thought. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.2:4.3"
msgid "Ettha vinodaya chandamanejo, "
msgstr "Unstirred, dispel desire for these things; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.2:4.4"
msgid "Yo ettha na limpati taṃ munimāhu. "
msgstr "for one called ‘a sage’ does not cling to them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.187, sc5
msgctxt "sn8.2:5.1"
msgid "Atha saṭṭhinissitā savitakkā, "
msgstr "Attached to the sixty wrong views, and full of their own opinions, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.2:5.2"
msgid "Puthū janatāya adhammā niviṭṭhā; "
msgstr "ordinary people are fixed in wrong principles. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.2:5.3"
msgid "Na ca vaggagatassa kuhiñci, "
msgstr "But that mendicant wouldn’t join a sectarian group, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.2:5.4"
msgid "No pana duṭṭhullabhāṇī sa bhikkhu. "
msgstr "still less would they utter lewd speech. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn8.2:6.1"
msgid "Dabbo cirarattasamāhito, "
msgstr "Clever, long serene, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.2:6.2"
msgid "Akuhako nipako apihālu; "
msgstr "free of deceit, alert, without envy, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.2:6.3"
msgid "Santaṃ padaṃ ajjhagamā muni paṭicca, "
msgstr "the sage has reached the state of peace; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.2:6.4"
msgid "Parinibbuto kaṅkhati kālan”ti. "
msgstr "and because he’s extinguished, he awaits his time.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
